    <br />
 <ul class="style18">
    <li class="style22">Students
must wear the formal uniform (Summer/Winter). Defaulters in
this respect are liable to be debarred from attending classes.</li>
    <li class="style22">Every student should carry school diary to the school each day along with his/her identity  card.</li>
    <li class="style22">The
    principal is empowered to rusticate or suspend or remove a student from
    the roll of the school on grounds of indiscipline use of unfair means
    in examinations, misbehavior, gross neglect of academic work or
    frequent absence without prior notice to the parents.</li>
    <li class="style22">Parents
    wishing to go round the school or meet the teacher must first obtain
    permission in writing from Principal.</li>
    <li class="style22">The school will  not be responsible for the loss of personal goods brought by the pupils.</li>
    <li class="style22">Students
    will be refrained from doing any damage to the school property
    (furniture, desks, chairs fans etc.), writing or drawing any thing on
    the walls or in any way damage things belonging to others.</li>
    <li class="style22">The
    students will not be permitted to leave the classes during the class
    hours without obtaining permission from the teacher concerned and
    without having class pass.</li>
    <li class="style22">No student will  manhandle any other student. Failure to do so may result in expulsion from  school.</li>
    <li class="style22">All
    students are required to participate in games and other activities.
    However if any child cannot do so on medical grounds, he/she shall have
    to take permission from the Principal.</li>
    <li class="style22">Lending or borrowing money among students is strictly  prohibited.</li>
    <li class="style22">Ingraham students should exhibit gentleman conduct and observe
    politeness wherever they go. They should greet &amp; extend full
    courtesy to the teachers when they meet them. Remember 'Manners Make
    A Man' . Use of foul language is not the sign of having been brought up
    in a decent home.</li>
  </ul>
